-- Pimco Total Return Fund had 15th month of outflows in July -Morningstar
-- By Jennifer Ablan
-- Mon Aug 04, 2014 10:38AM EDT
-- None



NEW YORK, Aug 4 (Reuters) - The Pimco Total Return Fund, the world's largest bond fund run by Bill Gross, had net outflows of $830 million July, marking its 15th straight month of outflows, according to Morningstar data on Monday.

The Pimco Total Return Fund had $223 billion in assets under management at the end of July, Morningstar said.